---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="SqueezyAgent Configuration"
  description="Draft configuration docs for SqueezyAgent."
  activeDoc="/docs/config/"
  heading="Configuration"
  lead="Configuration should keep provider access, budgets, permissions, and indexing behavior explicit."
>
  <section class="doc-block">
    <span class="status-pill">draft</span>
    <h2>Configuration areas</h2>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Providers</h3>
        <p>OpenAI Responses and Anthropic Messages streaming provider setup, routing defaults, and cache settings.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Budgets</h3>
        <p>Per-turn token limits, tool-result limits, and fallback thresholds.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Indexing</h3>
        <p>Repo roots, ignored paths, Rust semantic support, fallback languages, and graph freshness.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Permissions</h3>
        <p>Read, write, shell, web, and verification policy by agent mode.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Current runtime knobs</h2>
    <p>
      The foundation already exposes environment-driven controls for provider,
      model, max output tokens, parallel tool limits, spill thresholds, preview
      sizes, aggregate tool-result budgets, web permissions, and Exa MCP web
      search configuration.
    </p>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
